This paper deals with covert communication in the presence of an adversary, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also considers the use of a jammer, which falls under the category of network security (cs.NI) and system and control theory (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of block fading channels, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM) and wireless communication.
